description:
US military forces captured Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro and his wife, Cilia Flores, during a raid that followed what the president called "a large-scale strike" in the Venezuelan capital of Caracas. 

What to watch from a business perspective is that Venezuela is sitting on 303 billion barrels of oil. And what happens to that stockpile could impact global crude oil prices.
